  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide Oral Rehydration Points (ORP) in host community clinics in locations of Cholera outbreaks in Borno and Yobe States of north-east Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this UNICEF project is to provide lifesaving primary healthcare interventions in response to the cholera outbreak in Borno and Yobe States. With this CERF grant, UNICEF will procure and distribute 24 health kits and 540 cartons of 100 oral rehydration salts. The project will last six months and will benefit 239,901 people including 131,946 children.</narrative>
  </description>
